29 SUMMARY
3360 This bill creates the Learning Results Implementation Advisory Committee within the
3371 Department of Education to make recommendations on curricula, resources and staff
3382 training related to the study of racial and ethnic studies, financial literacy, civics and health
3393 care and to make recommendations on topics to be measured by learning indicators or to
4304 adjust learning indicators to reflect best practices. The bill appropriates $500,000 in fiscal
4315 year 2026-27 to provide grants to school administrative units and nonprofits to implement
4326 programs and learning activities based upon the committee's recommendation and
Page 2 - 132LR0904(01)

317 appropriates funds for an Interdisciplinary Instruction Specialist position. The bill also
328 directs the committee to include in the committee's recommendations the use of the
339 department's online, open-source education platform that provides optional resources at no
440 cost to educators in the State on topic areas and themes identified as areas of need by
451 educators.
